[11:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'reading further, I\'ll link to this main page in the description below. Also this week, we have this really cool project called Enhancing Spatial Under standing in image generation via reward modeling. In simple terms, this is basically a'

[12:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'framework that improves image generators so they can better understand spatial relationships in your prompt. For example, if you add words like left or right of something, behind something, above, below, then for most image models'

[12:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out there, it\'s not able to actually capture the position of everything that you specify. But, after adding this framework, it\'s a lot better. So, here are some examples. Let\'s say here\'s the text prompt, "In a dining room, a long'

[12:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'table holds three candles arranged in a line. From the viewer\'s perspective, the tallest candle is on the left, medium is in the center, shortest is on the right. We have a bowl of fruit sit sitting behind the center candle aligned with it. And then we have two plates placed'

[12:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in front of the line of candles, one aligned with the tallest and one aligned with the shortest. And then a painting hangs on the wall centered above the bowl." Now, here is the generation from just the raw flux model and as you can'

[12:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'see, the candles aren\'t arranged in a line, plus the tallest candle on the left, the bowl is not behind the center candle. There are just a lot of errors with this generation. However, if you use this new model, you can see that it'

[13:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually follows your prompt exactly. The candles are arranged in a line, we have the tallest candle on the left, there is a bowl of fruits behind the center candle, there is a plate in front'

[13:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of the left and the right candle. Plus, a painting is also centered and behind the center candle. It follows this perfectly. Or here\'s another example. Here we have an armchair faces a small round table, a floor lamp sits behind'

[13:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the chair aligned with its backrest center. A teacup sits on the table\'s left side, small plate of cookies sits on the table\'s right side, etc. etc. Now, again, here is the original image'

[13:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from Flux, but as you can see the lamp isn\'t actually behind the backrest of the chair, the cup isn\'t on the table\'s left side, and the cookies aren\'t on the right side. Whereas for this new method, you can see the lamp is indeed centered'

[13:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'behind the backrest of the chair, plus the items on the table are also arranged properly. Or here\'s another example where we have an orange cone centered behind a car, a backpack lies on the ground to the car\'s left rear tire, a'

[14:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
